2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of feedback channels in MIMO communication systems, which is a relevant topic in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper models the time evolution of MIMO channels as a Gauss-Markov process, which is a common technique in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with optimizing transmission rate in MIMO channels, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the design and implementation of communication systems in society.
